{
  "texts": [
    "In the case of Pynguin, the input strings it generated in Figure 1b represent a nonexistent device ('#O01E') and a directory that is defined in the Pynguin test environment ('/pynguin') that cover two of return behaviors in the focal method, but do not Fig. 2.",
    "Workflow for generating path constraint prompts.",
    "The focal method shown in Figure 1a is first parsed and its abstract syntax tree is traversed in preorder.",
    "In step 1 ○, the traversal first visits the first method statement, normalize_path(path), but does not record any information since it is not a branch constraint.",
    "In step 2 ○, it then traverses to the first if statement, and records that there is a constraint path.is_dir() that must be satisfied to execute the current path on the AST."
  ]
}